BEHIND THE LENS - THE CREW OF ‘IPSA’ | Garima Gautam (@garima_gautam), Manvi Dhall (@manvi_dhall) and Chahat Bawa (@chahatbawaa), Costume Department

This brilliant trio, led by Garima as the Costume Designer, worked tirelessly to create unique costumes that would meet the expectations of the film’s Ancient Indian setting, reflect the characters accurately and be comfortable for the cast to wear in the Indian heat. 

The result were some realistic and elegant costumes that enhanced the world of ‘IPSA’ immensely. 

All the costumes were hand-stitched by the tailor, Alam. The stylists, Chahat and Manvi, ably supported Garima and worked round-the-clock to assist the cast and bring the team’s vision to reality. 

Watch their efforts come to life in ‘IPSA’—streaming now on Klipist. Visit www.klipist.com or click the link in our bio to watch now! 

BTS images by Monica Dawar (@monica_dawar)
